name: Hideaway Residence Bali Ungasan
address: No. 168 Br. Kelod, Jl. Mengelak, Ungasan, South Kuta, Badung Regency, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
The location is good. However, the owner was very rude and careless. We tried to contact him with questions or complaints but received only hostile responses. Many issues had to be solved on their own.

The house was dirty, with stained linen. There is an additional fee for laundry. In addition, the presence of insects and the unpleasant smell of mold significantly worsened the stay experience. We are disappointed that our expectations for a pleasant stay were not met due to these negative issues
review 2:
In a less touristy part of Bali, security staff we're lovely.
We had mie goreng which was so delicious!
Bar staff also lovely!
review 3: Hideaway Residence Bali offers comfortable rooms and commendable services. However, the location lacks convenience, requiring some travel to major attractions. We booked a 2 nights stay for 2 rooms villa with pool, been upgraded to 3 rooms. The upgraded room at ground floor smell like newly paint odor from the bathroom. Other than that, the building and environment here are good. Grab food & Grab service are accessible to this area. Overall, it provides a pleasant retreat for those seeking a relaxing stay, but proximity to popular destinations may pose a slight inconvenience.  Anyhow, credit is due to the amazing host, Surya, who displayed exceptional hospitality amidst some of the property's shortcomings.
review 4:
Amazing! We stayed there for 17 days and had the best time. The place is new and clean. The breakfast was simply amazing and so worthy - with the best pancakes I‚Äôve ever had. Surya from the reception was extremely nice and polite - and took good care of us every day.
Would definitely come back!
review 5:
Great location in the heart of Bukit Uluwatu/Ungasan.
Close to GWK and Uluwatu Temple. Many cafe and restaurants can be found around this area. The place is also perfect for family or couple, long term or short term.

name: Roots Tree House
address: 55C6+95, Ungasan, South Kuta, Badung Regency, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Well, I think for one night it's very nice place and nature is amazing... but not more then that. It's not so comfortable when you can't take a shower in proper way. Especially if you traveling with a bf, it was challenging for me to use toilet. There is no AC, but fan is fine. Bug and mosquitoes nit bothering a lot when you are inside. Outside better to use spray. Service good, not bad not a best one. I like this place, but not for long term it was our mistake.
review 2:
Great place!! My son of 4 was so excited when he saw the tree house.. so nicely built with full of attention for details. It was so nice to wake up here. Even the shampoo smelled the bestüôèüèº

The breakfast was the bestüôèüèº all of the food was made so fresh and with pure ingredients

The staff was helpful and so kind.
If you look for a great get away, within nature and with luxury feeling. This is highly recommended!

It was so nice we rebooked for
More nights. Thanks team Roots for the great experience
review 3: I booked this place for a 2 night stay. It was one of the most pleasant and quiet places I‚Äôve stayed during my time in Bali. The treehouses are lovely, you will enjoy the lovely breeze in the evening/night. Do yourself a favor and treat yourself to a lovely rest and relaxation. Also, there‚Äôs loads of places to visit. I would advise renting a scooter or using Grab.
review 4:
Our first stop in Bali and unfortunately we left it too soon!!
Right from check-in we were made to feel right at home. Our flight was delayed twice, and eventually we got in at 2am and were  greeted with a warm smile and help with our bags and a tour of the treehouse.
We showered under the moonlight with the open air bathroom, and woke up to watching the Squirrels and birdsong. We can't believe that there were no bugs or mosquitos to worry about, and the fresh cool breeze was lovely.
This place is truly special, no matter which cabin you book. I can't believe we hesitated, it was one of our best ever stays. Thank you Roots team!
review 5: We visited here for acupuncture treatments with Tao acupuncture healing.  Diah was lovely, caring, knowledgeable and had a very healing experience. We met the owner Anna who was kind and generous. Looking forward to staying in the tree houses, looked beautiful. Very peaceful.

name: OYO Flagship 90756 Melasti Hills Room & Cafe
address: 1 Ungasan, Kuta Selatan, Bali, 0361, Jl. GWK Bali, Ungasan, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: Awful. The owner is a disaster, she doesnt even speak in english. After my booking confirmation arrived there (she did it to me 3 times already) she told me is fully booked‚Ä¶ even after booking it 4 days before‚Ä¶ and I perfectly know that is because she extend other guests face to face for more money than the app and she dont care about her bookings, just about the money. Then, cleaning service is terrible too. The smell in the bathroom is crazy bad. Never again here
review 2:
THIS IS A SCAM
We rented two rooms online, as we got there the lady told us there was no rooms left. The same thing happened to two other people as we were waiting to find a solution.
Someone told us it's a scam that they would tell booking or OYO that we never showed up so we have to pay 70% fees.

Only reason we stay to that place is because everything was fully booked in uluwatu. BIG SCAMMMMM ! Oh and also they asked us that we had to pay the room here. At the hotel by cash even if I showed the money they took in my bank account.
review 4:
TOURIST TRAP: after paying for the room online we were told we had to pay more than 50% extra. We were told that this was "company policy" however there was no mention of this online or anywhere else.

A shame because the hotel is clean and nice. However the service was terrible - we had to wait for half an hour for someone to turn up at the reception, we weren't given towels and we weren't allowed to leave our rucksacks.
review 5: I booked with agoda and payed online. When I first arrived the reception aas closed. When I came back one hour later, they told me all the rooms are booked out. So I had to find a new accomodation last minute. Very disappointing. I can not recommend it at all...

review 1: I live here. The units are average and not built well. So in rainy season they leak alot of get mould. But its a good location. There so many loose wires around that are a danger for kids. This place has massive potential. But as the units are so run down owners need to step up and sort out their investments. Before they become unliveable.
